visual_elements.description: Line drawing of a single-story house facade with a covered porch supported by columns. Labeled 'A Roofed porch'.

Line drawing of a two-story house facade with a prominent vaulted entry way featuring double doors and arched windows above. A vertical dimension line indicates 'Height greater than 12' above grade'. Labeled 'C Vaulted entry way'.

Line drawing of a house facade with a gabled roof and a small, gabled entry way to the right. A vertical dimension line indicates 'Height less than 12' above grade'. Labeled 'B Roofed entry way (not vaulted)'.

Line drawing of a building facade featuring a combination of a porch with arched openings and columns, and a vaulted entry way with an arched door. A vertical dimension line indicates 'Height greater than 12' above grade'. Labeled 'D Combination porch & vaulted entry way'.
A grey rectangular box containing text: 'See how to measure height of porches & entry features in Figs 6-8 on pp. 11-13'.
